VentureCrowd enables investors to access high return property development projects at all levels of the capital stack. We’ve built a full-scale property team that includes architects, engineers, developers and development managers with the ability to originate and manage end-to-end property development projects internally.

This allows us to have complete control over all aspects of the delivery, providing you with the trust that your investment is in expert hands.


Our due diligence is rigorous and our investment platform offers a seamless experience, making it safe and easy to manage your portfolio in one place. We’ve distributed over $20M in returns to property investors and we’re enabling more and more Australians to access the booming property sector.

componentInstanceProperties.name: label_Tab_1_Column_1
componentInstanceProperties.value: With real estate crowdfunding (also known as property crowdfunding), numerous investors contribute small amounts to purchase property or property development projects. A crowdfunding platform, like VentureCrowd, facilitates this, vets investment and development projects and brings investors together.

componentInstanceProperties.name: label_Tab_1_Column_2
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Traditional property investment requires a considerable amount of capital. Pooling funds from many investors makes property investment far more accessible. Investors can enter the property market from as little as $100 or $1,000 depending on the platform.

Find out more

componentInstanceProperties.name: label_Tab_2_Column_1
componentInstanceProperties.value:
With real estate crowdfunding you look for investments online, sign paperwork to invest in properties and development projects, transfer funds, and monitor how investments are going.

Property investments usually involve three parties: the sponsor, the platform, and the investor. The sponsor is the person or company who oversees the investment, buys the property, manages the property and/or development, and arranges for the eventual sale.

componentInstanceProperties.name: label_Tab_2_Column_2
componentInstanceProperties.value:
The crowdfunding platform is where sponsors and investors come together to raise capital. The platform evaluates projects and sponsors, ensures investors and deals meet requirements.

The investor is the party who contributes funds and receives income and/or a profit when the property sells at a profit.

Find out more

componentInstanceProperties.name: label_Tab_3_Column_1
componentInstanceProperties.value: Real estate crowdfunding provides a low-cost entry into the property market, allowing a wider range of investors to participate and diversify their portfolios. By investing smaller amounts in multiple projects, individuals can spread their risk and gain exposure to various locations. This approach offers the potential for passive income through rental yields or fixed interest returns.

componentInstanceProperties.name: label_Tab_3_Column_2
componentInstanceProperties.value:
The crowdfunding platform manages the funds, simplifying the investment process, and providing regular updates. With higher-yield returns compared to traditional options like term deposits, investors can enjoy potentially attractive returns. The flexibility of investing in both equity and debt investments allows for tailored strategies that balance risk and reward.

Find out more

componentInstanceProperties.value:
At VentureCrowd, we offer a unique approach to real estate crowdfunding whereby our property team comprises developers and end-to-end property managers to oversee the development of a project.

This enables us to manage the quality and feasibility of a project, from the selection of land development all the way through to the construction and eventual sale of the property.

componentInstanceProperties.name: label_Tab_4_Column_2
componentInstanceProperties.value:
On VentureCrowd, you invest in a fund that's managed by VentureCrowd under one of our two Australian Financial Services Licenses, or you invest in a proptech company that we are capital raising for.

We manage the investment on your behalf, so you don't need to deal with an underlying company. You simply monitor and manage your investment through your VentureCrowd investor dashboard, and we report back regularly to let you know how the project is progressing and pay returns into your nominated bank account.
